Buffalo Cauliflower Wings 🤝 Mother Raw Ranch 

You can’t judge a dressing by its appearance - it’s what’s on the inside that really counts! Our ranch may look different, but that’s because we include everything that’s good and skip what’s not. Here’s how to make it: 

INGREDIENTS:
Chopped Green Onion (¼ Cup)
Cauliflower Florets (1 Head of Cauliflower)

MARINADE:
Hot Sauce (½ Cup)
Jalapeño or Pickle Juice (1 Cup)
Vegetable Broth (1 Cup)
Black Salt (1 Tsp)

FLOUR MIXTURE:
Gluten Free Flour (3-4 Cups)
Smoked Paprika (2-3 Tbs)
Cayenne pepper (1-2 Tsp)
Garlic Powder (2-3 Tbs)
Poultry Seasoning (¼ Cup)
Onion Power (2-3 Tbs) 
Nutritional Yeast (4-6 Tbs)
Salt and Pepper to Taste

SWEET + SPICY BUFFALO SAUCE
Melted Vegan Butter (1.5 Cups)
Mustard (2 Tbs)
Buffalo Sauce (1 Cup)
Maple Syrup (1 Tbs)
Salt and Pepper

SERVE WITH:
#MotherRaw Ranch Dressing (1 Cup)

INSTRUCTIONS:
1️⃣ Heat your oven to 445F and line a baking sheet. 
2️⃣ Chop a head of cauliflower into bite-sized florets.
3️⃣ In a large bowl mix together coconut milk and Indian black salt. 
4️⃣ In a separate bowl mix together: gluten-free flour, smoked paprika, cayenne pepper, garlic powder, poultry seasoning, onion powder, nutritional yeast, salt, and pepper.
5️⃣ Dip and submerge your cauliflower pieces into the coconut milk mixture and then into the flour mixture. Tap excess off on the side of the bowl.
6️⃣ Place the coated cauliflower on a baking sheet. Bake for 15-20 mins at 445F degrees or until tender and soft.
7️⃣ In another bowl: mix together melted vegan butter, mustard, buffalo sauce, maple syrup, salt and pepper to taste to make the sweet and spicy buffalo sauce. 
8️⃣ When the cauliflower is baked, coat and cover in your sauce and add to a lined baking sheet.
9️⃣ Bake for 10-20 mins at 425 degrees and airfry them to make sure they are super crispy!
🔟 Once baked, transfer the buffalo cauliflower wings to a plate and sprinkle over some fresh chopped green onion. Serve with #MotherRaw Ranch for dipping!

CRISPY CHIPOTLE RICE DUMPLINGS 🔥
Hosting season is coming up! Save this shareable recipe for your next gathering!

INGREDIENTS
8-10 Sheets of Round Rice Paper
½ Cup Shaved Carrots
½ Cup Chopped Cabbage
½ Cup Sliced Radishes
1 Cup Minced Mushrooms 
½ Cup Sliced Bell Peppers
1.5 Cups Smashed Chickpeas

½ Cup Chopped Green Onions 
¼ Cup Sesame Seeds

DIRECTIONS
1️⃣ Make the Chipotle Sesame sauce by mixing together: chipotle dressing, liquid aminos, sesame oil, fresh ginger, green onions, and sesame seeds. 
2️⃣ Then mix together shaved carrots, sliced radishes, cabbage, minced mushrooms, sliced bell peppers, and smashed chickpeas. 
3️⃣ In a large pot, sauté minced garlic until lightly browned. Add in all of the chopped vegetables and season with a little bit of the Chipotle Sesame Sauce.
4️⃣ Cook the vegetables until slightly soft and seasoned with Chipotle Sesame Sauce.
5️⃣ Build the dumplings by first making a round piece of rice paper, damp with hot water. Only dip the rice paper in the water for less than 5 seconds. Place the damp rice paper on a flat surface and add a scoop of your sautéed veggie filling. One side at a time, fold the 4 sides of the rice paper into the middle to create a rectangular dumpling.
6️⃣ When all of the dumplings are folded and built, heat a large pot with a small bit of oil. 2-4 dumplings at a time, cook both sides of the dumpling for a few moments until browned and crispy on both sides. This can happen fast so be sure to watch over your pot!
7️⃣ Once the dumplings are cooked, garnish the plate with fresh greens and top the dumplings with sesame seeds and chopped green onions. Serve with a side of Chipotle Sesame dipping sauce.

4️⃣ Sprinkle over a layer of mixed vegan mozzarella, feta cheese, green onions, and repeat the potato, sauce, cheese, onion layering until you run out of sauce.
5️⃣ Garnish the top with cheese and chopped green onion.
6️⃣ Cover the glass pan with aluminum foil and bake the potatoes at 400°F for 50-65 minutes or until the potatoes are soft enough to easily pierce with a fork.

Are you ready for our plant-based take on this holly jolly holiday staple? 🥁🥁🥁 MUSHROOM WELLINGTON 🥁🥁🥁

INGREDIENTS:
Oil of Choice (3 Tbs)
Diced White Onions (½ Cup)
Chopped Mushrooms (4 Cups)
Crushed Pecans (2 Cups)
Cooked and Smashed Black Beans (2 Cups)
Steak Seasoning (3 Tbs)
Fresh Rosemary (4 Stems)
Maple Syrup (3 Tbs)
Mother Raw Balsamic Dressing (1 Bottle)
Salt and Pepper to Taste
Pastry Dough Sheets (3 Sheets)

INSTRUCTIONS:
1️⃣ Preheat the oven to 375°F to bake the Wellington. In the meantime, finely chop the mushrooms into small pieces.
2️⃣ In a large pot, sauté diced onions in oil until soft and translucent. Add chopped mushrooms, crushed pecans, smashed black beans, seasoning, and fresh rosemary. Mix well and let everything sauté and cook in the pot.
4️⃣ After about 3-5 minutes, when the mushrooms are cooked down and soft, add maple syrup and a bottle of Mother Raw Balsamic.
5️⃣ Cook everything together and cover the pot, letting it cook on medium heat for 5-10 minutes.
6️⃣ Once the mushrooms are cooked down in the seasoning, lay out your 3 sheets of pastry dough next to each other and roll them out with a rolling pin to make them thinner, longer, and stick together.
7️⃣ Once the dough forms one large rectangle, starting at the edge closest to you, fill up the middle of the edge with your mushroom-beef filling. Shape and form it into a thick round cylinder.
8️⃣ To close the dough, fold in the sides towards the mushroom-beef filling and carefully roll the filling into the dough, as if you are rolling a burrito away from you.
9️⃣ Once the dough fully wraps around the filling, place it on top of a covered baking sheet (seam facing down) and lightly score the dough diagonally with a knife to create a woven lattice texture.
🔟 Bake the Wellington for 15-25 minutes or until the dough is golden brown and crispy. You may have to cut the Wellington apart and bake the pieces individually to ensure they are fully cooked all the way through.
